body:
### Component

Forge

### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?

- [X] Foundry
- [X] Foundryup

### What version of Foundry are you on?

forge 0.2.0 (96ab913 2023-09-28T00:16:57.440609799Z)

### What command(s) is the bug in?

forge test

### Operating System

Linux

### Describe the bug

I'm unable to switch forks created in forge when using `vm.selectFork(forkId)`. I get the following error:
```The application panicked (crashed).
Message:  called `Option::unwrap()` on a `None` value
Location: crates/evm/src/executor/backend/mod.rs:663

This is a bug. Consider reporting it at https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry

  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ SPANTRACE ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

   0: evm::cheatcodes::fork
      at crates/evm/src/executor/inspector/cheatcodes/fork.rs:26
   1: evm::cheatcodes::apply
      at crates/evm/src/executor/inspector/cheatcodes/mod.rs:213

Backtrace omitted. Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.
Run with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.
Aborted
```

Steps to reproduce:
1. Do `forge init` and add the following text into `test/TestFork.t.sol`:
```// SPDX-License-Identifier: NONE
pragma solidity >=0.8.0 <0.9.0;

import "forge-std/Test.sol";

contract SimpleStorage {
    uint256 public value;
    function set(uint256 _value) external {
        value = _value;
    }
}

/// @dev start anvil --port 35353
contract TestFork is Test {
    function testFork() public {
        uint256 forkId1 = vm.createFork("http://localhost:35353");
        uint256 forkId2 = vm.createFork("http://localhost:35353");
        vm.selectFork(forkId1);
        SimpleStorage myContract = new SimpleStorage();
        emit log_address(address(myContract));
        vm.selectFork(forkId2);
        SimpleStorage myContract2 = new SimpleStorage();
        emit log_address(address(myContract2));
    }
}
```
3. Start a local anvil node using `anvil --port 35353`
4. In another terminal, run `forge test --mc TestFork`
